div.p: Task State Segment Ring 30 Stack Switching Mechanism

text.tspan: - Updated on EVERY context switch to user process

li.p: TSS is REQUIRED even for software task switching

ul.li: CPU uses SS0:ESP0 for stack switch on privilege change
Without valid TSS, any interrupt from ring 3 = Triple Fault

p.strong: Update ESP0 on EVERY context switch

ul.li: Each process has its own kernel stack
TSS.ESP0 must point to current process's kernel stack top
Modern OS uses one TSS for all processes
Only SS0:ESP0 fields are used by hardware
Other fields (ESP1/SS1, etc.) unused in most designs
